:: reforms
You turn inward, prioritizing the people's needs. Food is rationed fairly. Corrupt officials are removed. 

At first, progress is slow. The revolutionaries remain restless. 

Then, an opportunity arises: A popular rebel leader offers a truce. If you share power, they will support stability. 

What will you do? 

• [[Invite them into the government|share_power]]  
• [[Refuse and hold firm|hold_power]]  

:: share_power
The city is no longer yours alone. The people have a voice. 

Some of the council disapprove. But for now, peace holds. 

[[ending]]

:: hold_power
You refuse to compromise. The people, once hopeful, turn against you. 

The revolution reignites. Soon, the council falls. 

[[ending]]